==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sponging
<hw>Spon"ging</hw> <pr>(-j⟦icr⟧ng)</pr>, <def><pos>a. & n.</pos> from
<er>Sponge</er>, <pos>v.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Sponging house</b></col> <fld>(Eng. Law)</fld>, <cd>a
bailiff's or other house in which debtors are put before being taken to
jail, or until they compromise with their creditors. At these houses
extortionate charges are commonly made for food, lodging,
etc.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Spongiole</ent>⟦br⟧
